<br>
I think as well the low numbers has a small town effect. As you are not continually crowded and jostled, it is much easier to be friendly to the people you do meet.  Guilds are smaller and less people get lost in the cracks.  You do however as a result have to plan your activities more, you cant just count on going to a zone and joining in with people already there.<br>
<br>
And most of all I love that when I role play people do not look as if I have sprouted a second head and begun to babble <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
